title: Landslide events in the USA
name: Landslide events in the USA
description: Thirty-two individual landslides that are a representative sample of the most costly landslide events, and 15 landslides with the number of deaths and costs associated with these events.

properties.NAME: Madison
properties.REFERENCE: Wieczorek, G.F., Gori, P.L., Campbell, R.H., and Morgan, B.A. (1995)

properties.NAME: Hamilton
properties.COMMENTS: Many slides in soil and shale
properties.REFERENCE: 1.  Baum, R., and Johnson, A. (1996)    2.  Personal communication, Rich Pohana, Engineering Geologist

properties.NAME: camille
properties.COMMENTS: Most of the 150 who died were killed by broken bones and other blunt-force injuries, rather than by drowning

properties.NAME: Roosevelt
properties.COMMENTS: Failure caused by construction and filling and drawdown of Lake Roosevelt, Grand Coulee Dam, Washington
properties.REFERENCE: 1.  Jones, F.O., Embody, D.R., and Peterson, W.L. (1961)   2.  Schuster, R.L. (1979)

properties.NAME: northridge
properties.COMMENTS: 11,000 landslides over an area of 10,000 km2.  Most were in the Santa Susana Mtns., and in Mtns. north of Santa Clara River Valley.
properties.REFERENCE: 1.  Jibson, R.W., and E.L. Harp (1995)     2.  Jibson, R.W., and Harp, E.L., Schneider, E., Hajjeh, R.A. and Spiegal, R.A. (1998)  3.  Jibson, R.W., Harp, E.L., and Michael, J.A. (1998)

properties.NAME: SanDiego
properties.REFERENCE: Shearer, Clement, Taylor, F.A., and Fleming, R.W. (1983)

properties.NAME: SFBay97
properties.COMMENTS: Landslides triggered by El Nino rainstorms 1997-98
properties.REFERENCE: 1. Godt, J.W. (ed.) (1999)  2.  Godt, J.W. and Savage, W.Z. (1999)

properties.NAME: Wash96
properties.COMMENTS: Caused by winter storms on Febuary 5 - 9, 1996.
properties.REFERENCE: Harp, E.L., Chleborad, A.F., Schuster, R.L., Cannon, S.H., Reid, M.E., and Wilson, R.C. (1996)

properties.NAME: SFBay06
properties.COMMENTS: 11 deaths total/10 in Santa Cruz Mountains near Olive Springs, one 8 miles east of Hollister
